Create a data table with Controller AI Workbench styling:

1. **Component Structure:**
```tsx
import { DataTableFrame, StatusBadge, FinancialNumber } from '@/branding/ui';
import { Table, TableBody, TableCell, TableHead, TableHeader, TableRow } from '@/components/ui/table';
import type { [DataType] } from '@/lib/types';

interface [TableName]Props {
  data: [DataType][];
  title?: string;
  onRowClick?: (item: [DataType]) => void;
}

export function [TableName]({ data, title, onRowClick }: [TableName]Props) {
  return (
    <DataTableFrame
      title={title}
      showPagination={true}
      totalItems={data.length}
    >
      <Table>
        <TableHeader>
          <TableRow>
            <TableHead>Column 1</TableHead>
            <TableHead className="text-right">Amount</TableHead>
            <TableHead>Status</TableHead>
          </TableRow>
        </TableHeader>
        <TableBody>
          {data.map((item) => (
            <TableRow 
              key={item.id}
              onClick={() => onRowClick?.(item)}
              className="cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-50"
            >
              <TableCell>{item.name}</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-right">
                <FinancialNumber value={item.amount} />
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell>
                <StatusBadge status={item.status} variant="default" />
              </TableCell>
            </TableRow>
          ))}
        </TableBody>
      </Table>
    </DataTableFrame>
  );
}
```

2. **Styling Features:**
   - Premium card wrapper with pagination
   - Financial number formatting (right-aligned, tabular-nums)
   - Status badges with color coding
   - Hover effects and click handlers

3. **Required Elements:**
   - TypeScript interface for props
   - Proper data typing
   - Responsive design
   - Accessibility attributes

Create a KPI card following brand patterns:

1. **Component Structure:**
```tsx
import { KPICard, AgentBadge } from '@/branding/ui';
import { TrendingUp, TrendingDown } from 'lucide-react';

interface [CardName]Props {
  title: string;
  value: string | number;
  trend?: 'up' | 'down' | 'neutral';
  trendValue?: string;
  agentGenerated?: boolean;
  agentCode?: string;
  className?: string;
}

export function [CardName]({
  title,
  value,
  trend,
  trendValue,
  agentGenerated = false,
  agentCode,
  className
}: [CardName]Props) {
  const getTrendIcon = () => {
    if (trend === 'up') return <TrendingUp className="h-5 w-5 text-success" />;
    if (trend === 'down') return <TrendingDown className="h-5 w-5 text-danger" />;
    return null;
  };

  return (
    <KPICard
      title={title}
      value={value}
      trend={trend}
      trendValue={trendValue}
      variant="default"
      icon={getTrendIcon()}
      className={className}
    >
      {agentGenerated && (
        <div className="mt-2">
          <AgentBadge 
            agentCode={agentCode}
            status="completed"
            variant="subtle"
            size="sm"
          />
        </div>
      )}
    </KPICard>
  );
}
```

2. **Features:**
   - Premium card styling with hover effects
   - Trend indicators with icons and colors
   - AI agent attribution when applicable
   - Responsive design and accessibility

3. **Usage Guidelines:**
   - Use for key metrics and performance indicators
   - Include trend information when available
   - Show AI involvement with agent badges
   - Apply appropriate semantic colors

Create a chart component with Controller AI Workbench styling:

1. **Component Structure:**
```tsx
import { ChartFrame, ChartLegend } from '@/branding/ui';
import { CHART_COLORS } from '@/branding/ui';
import { 
  LineChart, 
  Line, 
  XAxis, 
  YAxis, 
  CartesianGrid, 
  Tooltip, 
  Legend,
  ResponsiveContainer 
} from 'recharts';

interface [ChartName]Props {
  data: Array<{
    name: string;
    value: number;
    // Add more data fields as needed
  }>;
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
  height?: number;
  showLegend?: boolean;
  className?: string;
}

export function [ChartName]({
  data,
  title,
  description,
  height = 300,
  showLegend = true,
  className
}: [ChartName]Props) {
  return (
    <ChartFrame
      title={title}
      description={description}
      height={height}
      className={className}
    >
      <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={height}>
        <LineChart data={data}>
          <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" stroke="#e5e7eb" />
          <XAxis 
            dataKey="name" 
            tick={{ fontSize: 12 }}
            stroke="#6b7280"
          />
          <YAxis 
            tick={{ fontSize: 12 }}
            stroke="#6b7280"
          />
          <Tooltip 
            contentStyle={{
              backgroundColor: 'white',
              border: '1px solid #e5e7eb',
              borderRadius: '8px',
              fontSize: '12px'
            }}
          />
          {showLegend && <Legend />}
          <Line 
            type="monotone" 
            dataKey="value"
            stroke={CHART_COLORS[0]}
            strokeWidth={2}
            dot={{ fill: CHART_COLORS[0], strokeWidth: 2 }}
          />
        </LineChart>
      </ResponsiveContainer>
    </ChartFrame>
  );
}
```

2. **Brand Requirements:**
   - MUST use ChartFrame wrapper
   - MUST use CHART_COLORS from brand tokens
   - Include responsive container
   - Apply consistent tooltip styling

3. **Chart Types Available:**
   - LineChart (trends over time)
   - BarChart (comparisons)
   - DonutChart (composition)
   - GaugeChart (KPI progress)
   - TreemapChart (hierarchical data)

Integrate AI agent features with brand compliance:

1. **Agent Badge Integration:**
```tsx
import { AgentBadge, AgentProcessIndicator } from '@/branding/ui';

// Add to component props
interface Props {
  // existing props...
  agentGenerated?: boolean;
  agentCode?: string;
  agentConfidence?: number;
  agentStatus?: 'idle' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'error';
  agentReasoning?: string[];
}

// In component JSX
{agentGenerated && (
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mt-2">
    <AgentBadge 
      agentCode={agentCode}
      status={agentStatus}
      confidence={agentConfidence}
      variant="subtle"
      size="sm"
    />
    {agentReasoning && (
      <span className="text-xs text-gray-500">
        {agentReasoning.length} reasoning steps
      </span>
    )}
  </div>
)}
```

2. **Process Indicator (for complex AI workflows):**
```tsx
<AgentProcessIndicator
  title="How AI Processes This Data"
  steps={[
    { step: "Data Analysis", status: "completed", confidence: 95 },
    { step: "Pattern Recognition", status: "completed", confidence: 88 },
    { step: "Recommendation Generation", status: "active", confidence: 92 },
    { step: "Validation", status: "pending" }
  ]}
/>
```

3. **Transparency Requirements:**
   - Show confidence levels when available
   - Provide "How AI..." explanations
   - Use agent purple color scheme
   - Include reasoning steps for complex processes

4. **Data Schema Updates:**
```tsx
