Update components to use brand-compliant colors:

1. **Color Token Replacement:**
```tsx
// Replace generic colors with brand tokens

// ❌ Before (generic colors)
className="bg-blue-500 text-white"
className="text-green-600"
className="border-red-500"

// ✅ After (brand colors)
className="bg-primary-500 text-white"          // Accenture purple
className="text-success"                       // Brand success green
className="border-danger"                      // Brand danger red
```

2. **Import Brand Colors:**
```tsx
import { BRAND_COLORS, CHART_COLORS, FINANCIAL_STATUS_COLORS } from '@/branding/ui';

// Use in components
const getStatusColor = (status: string) => {
  switch (status) {
    case 'completed': return FINANCIAL_STATUS_COLORS.completed;
    case 'inProgress': return FINANCIAL_STATUS_COLORS.inProgress;
    case 'blocked': return FINANCIAL_STATUS_COLORS.blocked;
    default: return FINANCIAL_STATUS_COLORS.notStarted;
  }
};
```

3. **Chart Color Updates:**
```tsx
// For Recharts components
<Line stroke={CHART_COLORS[0]} />              // Primary purple
<Bar fill={CHART_COLORS[1]} />                 // Secondary blue
<Area fill={BRAND_COLORS.success} />           // Success green

// Color sequence for multiple data series
colors={CHART_COLORS}  // [#8b5cf6, #3b82f6, #10b981, #f59e0b, #ef4444, #6b7280]
```

4. **CSS Variable Updates:**
```css
/* Update custom CSS to use brand variables */
:root {
  --primary: 262 83% 58%;        /* Accenture purple in HSL */
  --success: 156 73% 52%;        /* Brand success green */
  --warning: 32 95% 44%;         /* Brand warning amber */
  --danger: 0 84% 60%;           /* Brand danger red */
}
```

5. **Status Badge Updates:**
```tsx
const getStatusVariant = (status: string) => {
  switch (status) {
    case 'completed': case 'posted': return 'success';
    case 'pending': case 'in-progress': return 'warning';
    case 'rejected': case 'error': return 'danger';
    case 'draft': return 'info';
    default: return 'default';
  }
};
```
